</head>

<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/real-estate" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Real Estate</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">First-Time Landlord Tips</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                Essential Tips for First-Time Landlords: A Survival Guide
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/first-time-landlord-tips.webp"
                                    alt="Landlord and tenant signing a lease agreement"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    Becoming a landlord can be a great way to build wealth, but it also comes with a
                                    host of responsibilities and potential pitfalls. Proper preparation and a
                                    professional approach are key to being successful and avoiding common mistakes.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Tenant Screening is Vital</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Your tenant can make or break your rental experience.
                                    Always perform a thorough background and credit check.</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Credit Score:</strong> A good credit history indicates financial
                                        responsibility.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Employment Verification:</strong> Ensure they have a steady income.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Previous Landlord References:</strong> Check their rental history and
                                        behavior.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Understanding Legal Requirements
                                </h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Familiarize yourself with local, state, and federal fair
                                    housing and landlord-tenant laws to protect yourself and your tenants.</p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Maintenance and Insurance</h2>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Landlord Insurance:</strong> Get specific coverage for rental
                                        properties.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Regular Inspections:</strong> Schedule periodic walkthroughs to identify
                                        maintenance issues.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Emergency Fund:</strong> Have money set aside for unexpected repairs.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    Being a landlord is a business. Treat it with professionalism, keep good records,
                                    and maintain clear communication with your tenants to ensure a positive experience
                                    for everyone involved.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
                        <div class="sticky top-8 space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Legal Tip</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-600">Always use a legally binding lease agreement that clearly
                                    outlines responsibilities, rent amounts, and security deposit rules.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
